HEADWORD: Caterpillar track
<hw>Cat"er*pil`lar track</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>an
endless belt looped over several wheels, used in pairs in place of
wheels to propel vehicles, such as tractors or military tanks, over
rough ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

